	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Saralin,<br><br>My suggestion for soloing as a level 30 Paladin? If you want adventure, risk and fun...I suggest the second floor of Unrest!&nbsp;&nbsp;That's right, Unrest. At 30 you can solo several mobs on the second floor.  There are two rooms with single mobs and 2 single mobs that wander the hallways of the second floor.  There is also the one mob  that spawns near the Gnome Necro that is out in the open, but as long as you have taken out the single wandering mob in that hallway, you can take him out too.  Just make sure you have your stun and root ready because the C. Ghouls will run when they get low on pts.<br><br>It definitely has a big element of risk, but with a little practice it can be quite productive and the money is good too!  I did it....you can too!<br><br>Just something to think about....<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br>Fifth Column<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
