	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're calling me an idiot...<br><br>I still get a rebuttal. :P<br><br>All right.&nbsp;&nbsp;I melee just like a warrior (except with a shield instead of another sword).  I am healing myself and yaulping constantly.  When I'm really low on health and can't heal myself/am oom, I LoH.  If I can manage it and am not lom, I root and back off to heal before then.  It simply depends on the situation.  That is how I solo.<br><br>I soloed mobs in Mistmoore for 4 hours on Sunday and went all the way from 1 yellow into 28 to 29.  We are easily as tough as a warrior.  If you know how to use your spells.  I've been a major proponent of the saying "you have to kill us twice."  The most downtime I had the entire time was five minutes.  The only times I ever had to zone were for other people's trains, and those only rarely because I was the only person in the zone the entire time.  I was even double pulling.<br><br>I have always believed in the philosophy that we are 25% cleric, 75% warrior.  We fight much better than we heal.  Our main purpose in a fight is to use those swords and lances we carry around.  They aren't decoration.<br><br>Yes, we are our own unique class.  Strategies on other classes don't work with us.  We can solo, we can tank, we can heal.  After a long battle, I'm usually the one healing the rest of the party because the cleric has no mana.<br><br>Don't accuse us of being purely casters.  Don't accuse us of being purely warriors.  We combine the best parts of both classes into a new whole.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonfury<br>Crusader of the Burning Heart, 60th Protection, Third Blessing<br>Fennin Ro<br>New Dawnings<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479</a></td></tr>
