<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=100242646666728></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100242646666728><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100242646666728>How to Get Cash-Part 1</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100242646666728#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6400><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>100 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 6th 11:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello Everybody, to summorize this post, it will hopefully be a long one, it will be about making cash for the first 20 levels or your EQ Life, this will work for almost any class(tanks preferably-bards best), but may require some traveling from where you are. I am writing this guide to help all of you young players out there who want that nice weapon of so bad, but can't figure out how to get it with minimal work. Well, i have played every single class to level 10 at least, and needless to say, this WORKS. So, here it is, your referencial guide on the DO's and DONT's of making money-Part 1.<br><br>Section 1. Starting Zones.<br> Ok this is about starting zones in my opinion. These will be ranked from 1-3, 1 being the best in terms of cash flow from there. THESE ARE ZONES THAT ARE REALLY FROM 1-5 WITH SOME EXCEPTIONS.<br><br>1. Paineel.-In my experience, this is crazy cash flow if you know how to do it. I started out here just hunting Decaying Skellies and gathering all my bone chips. You may not get to sell em here, but if you do, People from the Hole will gladly pay 10pp per stack! I made about 250pp in levels 1-5 here. Unparalled in cash for those levels.<br><br>2. EverFrost.-INCREDIBLE place to begin for cash making. Plenty of Skellies around for bone Chips-even though they only sell 3pp a stack here. Polar Bears of any type drop HQ Bear Pelts uncommonly but they sell for 30pp a pop. At leve; 10 from hunting just Skellies and Bears i had about 250pp and i bought a weapon worth 100pp for my shammy.<br><br>3. Greater Faydark.-Incredible place to start out in. You can get to 9 just hunting Orcs here with a TON of cash making involved. Even though i recommend going to ButcherBlock first and gathering up exp in there till 6 where you can hunt Orc Centaurions for their belts which sell for 1pp each. If you do this till level 9 you should have about 300pp from belts alone.<br><br>Section 2. Starting Suggestions of Money Making(1-5).<br> First off, if are not KoS in these starting places, i suggest you make the journey over to one of them and hunt there till you feel you have outgrown the zone. Without Further Adue-how to make money levels 1-5.<br><br>1. Kill every single Decaying Skeleton you can find. Save their bone chips and DO NOT sell them to the merchants. Save them up until you see someone auctioning to buy them. Charge 3-6pp per stack unless a high lvl necro or other class is buying them, then ask them if they wouldnt mind paying 1-3pp extra per stack. <br><br>2. If your Zone has bears that are killable at earlier levels, Kill every single bear you can find-green or not. If they drop LQ/MQ pelts, sell them to merchants. If they drop HQ Bear pelts, save those up until someone wants to buy em, then sell those to them for 30pp per pelt.<br><br>3. Find Skellies with Weapons. Besides killing every skelly you find, if they have a weapon loot it and sell it to those merchants. Some weapons go for 2 gold. Those add up.<br><br>4. Kill Bats. Save up their batwings and sell them to people who wanna buy them. 2pp per stack is the norm.<br><br>5. Kill EVERYTHING that moves and loot EVERYTHING. sell stuff that wont sell to other people to merchants. This is an ok way that is somewhat quick and nets you the most exp, but not as much cash.<br><br>Section 3. How to make money. (9-15)<br> In this section i will tell you the secrets of making money that will supply you with your equip to level 30 in most cases.<br><br>1. MOVE TO EAST COMMONS, or EVERFROST. These are 2 of the safest, BEST places for cash at these levels.<br><br>2. THE Money Making guide. First off, you need to know how to play your character to survive this, as it will be trying your skills and will teach you how to play efficiently. Thta said, the first thing you should do if make your way out to the tunnel and ask for a SoW, and some hp buffs. Usually a nice neighboorhood druid will come around around and buff you extremely well. Then what you wanna do is go over to Orc 1. DO NOT GET IN A GROUP HERE. <br> Ok, what you do is run around and find either a black bear, a Young Kodiak that doesnt con red, or a willowisp that doesnt con red. To kill wisps, you need a magical weapon. If you are a tank class and have some pp, buy either an Axe of the Iron Back(2hs) for 30pp or something like a PGT(1hs)for 50pp-100pp. Anyways with buffs you should be able to take these down. Save every single Greater Lightstone you get for further use. If you happen to get a HQ bear Pelt, sell it for 30pp. At any rate, you should get around 2 bear pelts at level 9 since the YKs con high yellow-red and give loads of exp, and about 4-6 every level after. At 10 you should be able to take down YKs and Wisps very easily really, and you should get a good amount of money for these. Also, if you want more GLSs or just more things to kill with a bit higher risk, go over to West Commons-ill explain later. You should hunt in East Commons until 12 and by then you should have amassed around 600pp if you do this right and don't spend anything which is highly doubtable. Anyways at levels 11/12-15 you should most definatly hunt in West Commons. The area you want to go to is from the tollbooth to the Inn where the tonsmiths are. I nicknamed this spot Wisp Highway. Almost every Wisp in the zone comes through this area which means that your exp should be movin and your backpacks should be filling up with GLSs. Also, be careful since the guards at the booth wont kill Wisps so dont get more than 2 on you unless you are around level 14. YKs and Black Bears sometimes wander through here which makes getting money on the spot a little bit easier but you are not getting as much since Wisps are your primary exp source atm. At 15 some Wisps are starting to green out along with YKs. Time to move on out. This is gonna be why you saved your GLSs, and youll thank me too.(Note on EverFrost-Just do everything here cept just kill Polar Bears and Mammoth Calves or whatever cons near your level.)<br><br>Section 4. How to Make Money.(15-20)<br>Well, pack up your backpacks full of Greater Lightstones and head on down to Oasis of Marr. Many people critisize this zone for being overused and frankly, it is. But who cares when this is crazy exp and some of the best money for these levels too. First off, go over to the Gypsy camp and head on over to Synthia or some gypsy named like that. Pay one person some pp to hold a bag for a bit for you at the Gypsy camp. Then turn in the Greater Lightstones one by one to her, each time getting a container which sells for 7-10pp to her. keep doing this and then ask for your bag back from the dude and keep doing this with all your GLSs. After doing this run back to your bank in FP or wherever you bank, and turn in your money. I made 800pp just off of Wisp hunting in 6 levels using this strategy. Then either head on over to HighPass and get in an Orc or Gnoll group for nice loots and ok exp, or go back to Oasis and get in Orc Highway groups over there. Either way you should get a fair amount of money in those 5 levels-around 400pp really. HighPass is better for loot, Oasis is for exp. Either way you can still make your way into level 20 with MUNDO plat for your level.<br><br>Section 5. Alternative Money Making.(Smithing)<br> One more way which you should do if you are a tank, is start smithing at level 20. Use all of your money on smithing and you should be making banded and maybe a couple of peices of Fine Plate Armor. Not too bad considering some FP peices sell for 100pp normally. You can lose all of your money on smithing just to gain it back from FP armor, plus you can supply yourself with money without hunting and armor for a long time to come.<br><br>And now i come to an end of writing this post as a guide as many people have asked on boards like this one how to get money to buy nice stuff early on. Thank you all for reading this through and i hope it helps.<br><br>Zomor Soulsaver<br>Champions of Brell-51st Season<br>"Thunder is impressive, but Lightning gets the job done."<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
