	   <tr><td colspan=2>Excuse me?<br><br>I solo effectively all the time.&nbsp;&nbsp;In a given level, I am more likely to gain two or three orange from soloing than in groups.  I keep my casting skills maxed because they're necessary.<br><br>But I am a meleer and damage sponge, above all else.  In a given fight, I am more likely to take damage than any warrior we have.  And I will last longer, because I know how to fight effectively, how to conserve my LoH, and how to cast when it's necessary.  Sometimes, I am the only tank we have.  I do very nice damage, especially against undead, with my new Ghoulbane.<br><br>We can perform equally well with or without a group behind us.  Yes, we'll have more downtime without.  But I never really worry about it.<br><br>Besides.  If you heard about my character, you'd think that paladins never roleplay.<br><br>*drinks yet another stack of Elven*<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonfury<br>Crusader of the Burning Heart, 60th Protection, Third Blessing<br>Fennin Ro<br>New Dawnings<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479</a></td></tr>
